267
00:38:46,538 --> 00:38:47,997
Thanks for showing up, Jorge.

268
00:38:53,962 --> 00:38:56,506
Sir, we don't know how much the DEA knows.

269
00:38:56,673 --> 00:39:00,552
We need to assume
all your current homes are... unsafe.

270
00:39:03,096 --> 00:39:04,597
I'll stay here for now.

271
00:39:10,019 --> 00:39:10,895
We all need to talk.

272
00:39:15,191 --> 00:39:18,194
What did you expect? A warrant
by definition authorizes the police...

273
00:39:20,029 --> 00:39:23,825
Wait. Let's not lie to ourselves.

274
00:39:23,992 --> 00:39:27,579
This operation was run
by the Drug Enforcement Administration

275
00:39:27,745 --> 00:39:28,997
of the United States.

276
00:39:29,163 --> 00:39:32,000
The takedown, Mr. Attorney General,
was National Police.

277
00:39:32,584 --> 00:39:34,377
The transport was by our police.

278
00:39:34,544 --> 00:39:36,629
The booking was by our police.

279
00:39:36,796 --> 00:39:39,173
So a war started by National Police?

280
00:39:39,340 --> 00:39:41,509
Look, as Attorney General,

281
00:39:41,676 --> 00:39:44,679
my main... concern is achieving
a peaceful settlement with the godfathers.

282
00:39:47,265 --> 00:39:49,726
And the arrest
of Gilberto Rodriguez Orejuela

283
00:39:49,893 --> 00:39:53,688
means we now have new leverage
to negotiate with.

284
00:39:54,772 --> 00:39:57,901
The President of Colombia, Ernesto Samper.

285
00:40:02,906 --> 00:40:04,991
I hate to be late to a good debate.

286
00:40:05,491 --> 00:40:08,995
You know us, might as well
try to smooth rough water with a hammer.

287
00:40:12,040 --> 00:40:13,833
I've been apprised by Minister Botero

288
00:40:14,000 --> 00:40:16,628
about our newly-incarcerated
Cali godfather.

289
00:40:17,420 --> 00:40:21,215
-With all due respect, Mr. President?
-Go ahead, Miguel.

290
00:40:22,383 --> 00:40:26,137
We've worked for months
to negotiate this surrender.

291
00:40:27,347 --> 00:40:30,725
We recommend the immediate release
of Mr. Rodriguez Orejuela.

292
00:40:33,436 --> 00:40:35,271
Colombia is a nation of laws.

293
00:40:36,356 --> 00:40:37,732
Not of concessions.

294
00:40:38,983 --> 00:40:41,819
If I give a pass to the largest criminal
organization in the world...

295
00:40:42,862 --> 00:40:45,573
the trust of the people
will be lost forever.

296
00:40:48,284 --> 00:40:50,662
Mr. Rodriguez is entitled
to the same due process

297
00:40:50,828 --> 00:40:52,789
as any Colombian citizen.

298
00:40:54,040 --> 00:40:56,292
Let's see where due process gets him.

299
00:40:59,253 --> 00:41:00,254
For now...

300
00:41:02,090 --> 00:41:03,591
his arrest stands.

301
00:41:05,009 --> 00:41:06,094
Thank you, gentlemen.

302
00:41:25,697 --> 00:41:27,031
Thank you very much.

303
00:41:59,731 --> 00:42:03,568
We talked about this.
I don't want the stink of this on you.

304
00:42:03,735 --> 00:42:04,736
Relax, Dad.

305
00:42:05,153 --> 00:42:08,781
I'm a lawyer. I'm the only one
in the family who can visit you.

306
00:42:12,577 --> 00:42:15,580
Besides, I thought you could use
a friendly face.

307
00:42:18,332 --> 00:42:21,335
What I could really use
is a tumbler of whiskey about this big.

308
00:42:28,551 --> 00:42:29,510
How's it look?

309
00:42:31,596 --> 00:42:33,347
The warrants are old.

310
00:42:34,891 --> 00:42:37,185
-Invalid?
-Vulnerable.

311
00:42:38,603 --> 00:42:42,065
I have a lunch tomorrow at 1:00 pm.
with the Colombian Board of Pharmacies.

312
00:42:42,231 --> 00:42:44,233
8:00 a.m., latest, I'm out.

313
00:42:45,151 --> 00:42:48,154
Dad, you're here until our lawyers
get you in front of a judge.

314
00:42:48,821 --> 00:42:51,824
And he'll hold you here in Bogotà
due to the conspiracy charge.

315
00:42:54,952 --> 00:42:56,120
I don't get it.

316
00:42:56,704 --> 00:42:58,790
This is a mistake, a blunder.

317
00:42:58,956 --> 00:43:02,543
A gross overstep
by a rogue American agent!

318
00:43:03,127 --> 00:43:05,046
That's what you want to believe.

319
00:43:05,296 --> 00:43:07,340
But if that was the case,
you'd be out by now.

320
00:43:10,718 --> 00:43:13,387
-Dad, this is real.
-No, money is real.

321
00:43:13,554 --> 00:43:15,431
And what about all I've paid?

322
00:43:16,766 --> 00:43:19,519
Sons of bitches
can't leave me confined here.

323
00:43:23,523 --> 00:43:26,901
How the fuck did they surprise us
like that, gentlemen?

324
00:43:27,527 --> 00:43:28,569
It was Calderón.

325
00:43:31,197 --> 00:43:33,366
Dad, I say we tear him to pieces.

326
00:43:33,950 --> 00:43:36,953
-And his fucking family and his children.
-David, please.

327
00:43:38,496 --> 00:43:41,666
Obviously, there's responsibility
on all sides.

328
00:43:43,000 --> 00:43:45,962
-Cordova...
-Sir, just as we realized...

329
00:43:46,129 --> 00:43:47,421
By the time you realized,

330
00:43:47,588 --> 00:43:50,591
Colonel Martinez had already been
in my brother's house for 30 minutes.

331
00:43:53,219 --> 00:43:55,721
Don Miguel. The failure's mine.

332
00:43:55,888 --> 00:43:58,474
When it comes to the DEA,
Cordova counts on me.

333
00:44:00,893 --> 00:44:03,896
Wait. Cordova, you're my brother's
personal head of security.

334
00:44:06,732 --> 00:44:07,733
Yes, sir.

335
00:44:08,484 --> 00:44:10,653
Then you should've been there.

336
00:44:11,946 --> 00:44:15,408
Your men should've been there.

337
00:44:16,576 --> 00:44:19,579
Your guards were fooled
by a fucking chicken truck.

338
00:44:22,915 --> 00:44:25,168
I want to know what the fuck
is happening here.

339
00:44:25,793 --> 00:44:28,796
Because I'm starting to believe
that none of us are safe.

340
00:44:32,425 --> 00:44:33,384
Not your families...

341
00:44:37,889 --> 00:44:38,848
and not mine.

342
00:44:40,224 --> 00:44:41,267
My family.

343
00:44:47,273 --> 00:44:50,860
Thank you, Attorney General Valdivieso,
Defence Minister Botero.

344
00:46:16,487 --> 00:46:18,239
Colonel, please.

345
00:46:19,073 --> 00:46:20,366
Thanks.

346
00:46:39,135 --> 00:46:40,469
